&lt;p&gt;The Executive Assistant will play a critical role in helping executives operate efficiently, stay organized, and remain focused on strategic priorities. The right candidate will bring strong judgment, exceptional attention to detail, discretion in handling confidential information, and the ability to interact professionally with senior leaders, advisors, clients, and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
